    "body": "Thanks for reporting this @mshakeg, I can confirm it's happening. As a workaround, you can create a file in your project that only imports the lib contract you want to flatten. For example, create a `contracts/ProxyAdmin.sol` file with:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nimport \"@openzeppelin/contracts/proxy/transparent/ProxyAdmin.sol\";\r\n```\r\n\r\nand then `hh flatten contracts/ProxyAdmin.sol`. The result will not be _exactly_ the same as the one you'd get by flattening the lib file, but it will be almost the same, so depending on your use case it might be enough.",
